<?xml version="1.0" encoding="ASCII"?>
<caldef:CalDefinitionFile xmlns:caldef="http://www.caltools.gm.com/caldef" xmlns:xsi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance" Description="This file contains calibrations for center stack display gesture performances and various timeouts, such as popup autodismiss timeouts.">
  <CalDefFileVersion>16</CalDefFileVersion>
  <CalDefFileChangeRecord>
    <Version>2</Version>
    <Date>24APR14</Date>
    <Description>Initial Version.</Description>
    <Author>Andrew Gellatly</Author>
  </CalDefFileChangeRecord>
  <CalDefFileChangeRecord>
    <Version>3</Version>
    <Date>29SEP14</Date>
    <Description>Add Usage on all components</Description>
    <Author>Scott Rush</Author>
  </CalDefFileChangeRecord>
  <CalDefFileChangeRecord>
    <Version>4</Version>
    <Date>13OCT14</Date>
    <Description>Fixed Name errors that prevented use of code generation.</Description>
    <Author>Scott Rush</Author>
  </CalDefFileChangeRecord>
  <CalDefFileChangeRecord>
    <Version>5</Version>
    <Date>2/24/2015</Date>
    <Description>Just revised change history on cals where appropriate to show which cals are applicable to GIS-500.</Description>
    <Author>Ginnard Kimbrough</Author>
  </CalDefFileChangeRecord>
  <CalDefFileChangeRecord>
    <Version>6</Version>
    <Date>4/21/2015</Date>
    <Description>In this Caldef file, deleted the POP_UPS_WIDGET_AUTOMATIC_DISMISSAL_TIME_2 and POP_UPS_WIDGET_AUTOMATIC_DISMISSAL_TIME_3 cals since these cals are duplicate cals to the POP_UPS_WIDGET_AUTOMATIC_DISMISSAL_TIME_1 cal already released in this caldef file. Also changed the name of the cal POP_UPS_WIDGET_AUTOMATIC_DISMISSAL_TIME_4 cal to POP_UPS_WIDGET_AUTOMATIC_DISMISSAL_TIME_2 since the previous released cals, POP_UPS_WIDGET_AUTOMATIC_DISMISSAL_TIME_2 and POP_UPS_WIDGET_AUTOMATIC_DISMISSAL_TIME_3, that were duplicated cals are being deleted.</Description>
    <Author>Ginnard Kimbrough</Author>
  </CalDefFileChangeRecord>
  <CalDefFileChangeRecord>
    <Version>7</Version>
    <Date>7/10/2015</Date>
    <Description>Per feedback from Cody Hansen made the following updates in this Caldef file: 1.) Re-added the POP_UPS_WIDGET_AUTOMATIC_DISMISSAL_TIME_2, POP_UPS_WIDGET_AUTOMATIC_DISMISSAL_TIME_3, and POP_UPS_WIDGET_AUTOMATIC_DISMISSAL_TIME_4 CALs that were deleted  in the initial MY18 CAL Database Release in revision 6 of this CalDef file that was used for that CAL database release since it's been confirmed these CALs are now still needed, and updated the description for the POP_UPS_WIDGET_AUTOMATIC_DISMISSAL_TIME_1, POP_UPS_WIDGET_AUTOMATIC_DISMISSAL_TIME_2, POP_UPS_WIDGET_AUTOMATIC_DISMISSAL_TIME_3, and POP_UPS_WIDGET_AUTOMATIC_DISMISSAL_TIME_4 CALs to match the description shown in the GIS-500 Version 3.0,  June 26, 2015. 2.) Updated resolution for the FACEPLATE_VOLUME_STEP_PER_SLIDER_SENSOR and VOLUME_PRESS_HOLD_VOLUMESLEWRATE CALs within this Caldef file  from 10 to 1 to be able to set these CALs to the same value used for current production that is yielding optimized performance for faceplate volumn adjustements. Also, updated the default values for the following CALs: ENABLE_FACEPLATE_VOLUME_PRESS_HOLD (change default value from false to true), ENABLE_FACEPLATE_VOLUME_TAP CALs (changed default value from False to True), POP_UPS_WIDGET_AUTOMATIC_DISMISSAL_TIME_1 (changed default value from 20 to 60 ), POP_UPS_WIDGET_AUTOMATIC_DISMISSAL_TIME_2 (changed default value from 10 to 6), ENABLE_REVEALON_APPROACH (changed the default value from DEFAULT (Value = 0xFF) to a value of ON (Value = 0x1) ). 3.) Deleted the following legacy CALs that are no longer needed for Info. 3.0: CHEVY_APPS_TRAY_INACTIVITY_TIMER, ENABLE_AUDIONOWPLAYING_SENDTOCLUSTER, HOME_SCREEN_TIMEOUT, and ENABLE_APPTRAY_NAV_MODE_QSP.  4.) Also, deleted the ENABLE_REVEALONAPPROACHFADEOUT CAL from this CalDef file since it is not being used and is not necessary, given there is already another ENABLE_PROXIMITY_SENSING calibration. </Description>
    <Author>Ginnard Kimbrough</Author>
  </CalDefFileChangeRecord>
  <CalDefFileChangeRecord>
    <Version>8</Version>
    <Date>9/3/2015</Date>
    <Description>Within this CalDef file made the following updates: 1.) Changed the CAL name of the FACEPLATE_FLING_MIN_SLIDER_POSITIONS CAL from FACEPLATE_FLING_MIN_SLIDER_POSITIONS to FACEPLATE_FLING_MIN_VOLUME_POSITIONS, updated the CAL description for this CAL, and changed the CAL default value from 2 to 10 to match the actual implementation of this CAL. 2.) Changed the CAL name of the MAX_FACEPLATE_VOLUME_SLIDER_SENSORS CAL from MAX_FACEPLATE_VOLUME_SLIDER_SENSORS to MAX_FACEPLATE_VOLUME_POSITIONS, updated the CAL description for this CAL, and changed the CAL default value from 12 to 63 to match the actual implementation of this CAL. 3.) Changed the CAL name of the FACEPLATE_VOLUME_STEP_PER_SLIDER_SENSOR CAL from FACEPLATE_VOLUME_STEP_PER_SLIDER_SENSOR to FACEPLATE_SLIDER_POSITIONS_PER_VOLUME_STEP, updated the CAL description for this CAL, and changed the CAL default value from 2 to 3 to match the actual implementation of this CAL. 4.) Updated the description for the VOLUME_PRESS_HOLD_VOLUMESLEWRATE CAL to match the actual implementation of this CAL. 5.) Updated the description for the FACEPLATE_TAP_MAX_TIME CAL, and changed the CAL default value from 1500 to 1000  to match the actual implementation of this CAL. 6.) Per request from Sanghyun Ryu, updated CAL usage for the APPLICATION_REVEALONAPPROACHTIME CAL to not show Low Radio usage. </Description>
    <Author>Ginnard Kimbrough</Author>
  </CalDefFileChangeRecord>
  <CalDefFileChangeRecord>
    <Version>9</Version>
    <Date>12/1/2015</Date>
    <Description>Based on feedback received from Jideok Son, made usage correction to remove Low Radio usage for the following calibrations: FACEPLATE_SLIDER_POSITIONS_PER_VOLUME_STEP, ENABLE_REVEALONAPPROACH, ENABLE_PROXIMITY_SENSING, REVEALONAPPROACHFADEOUTTIME, MAX_FACEPLATE_VOLUME_POSITIONS, and CSHMI_AUX_TOUCH_EVENT_BUFFER_TIME calibrations within this CalDef file.</Description>
    <Author>Ginnard Kimbrough</Author>
  </CalDefFileChangeRecord>
  <CalDefFileChangeRecord>
    <Version>10</Version>
    <Date>2/26/2016</Date>
    <Description>Within this caldef file, updated the default value for the FACEPLATE_FLING_MIN_VOLUME_POSITIONS CAL from 10 to 5, updated default value of the FACEPLATE_TAP_MAX_TIME CAL from 1000 to 500,updated the default value of the VOLUME_PRESS_HOLD_VOLUMESLEWRATE CAL from 250 to 50. Based off of feedback received from Cody Hansen that this is the most optimal value to set this value to at this point.</Description>
    <Author>Ginnard Kimbrough</Author>
  </CalDefFileChangeRecord>
  <CalDefFileChangeRecord>
    <Version>11</Version>
    <Date>1/13/2017</Date>
    <Description>Within the DisplayGesturesAndTimeouts.caldef file made the following updates: Updated the default value for the FACEPLATE_FLING_MIN_VOLUME_POSITIONS calibration from a value of 5 to 2 to match the optimized value it was determined this calibration needed to be set to for MY17. Updated the units reflected for the POP_UPS_WIDGET_AUTOMATIC_DISMISSAL_TIME_1, POP_UPS_WIDGET_AUTOMATIC_DISMISSAL_TIME_2, POP_UPS_WIDGET_AUTOMATIC_DISMISSAL_TIME_3, and POP_UPS_WIDGET_AUTOMATIC_DISMISSAL_TIME_4  calibrations from none to seconds to match the units that were always reflected for these calibration in the GIS-500. Updated the units for the ALERTWINDOWELEMENT_DELAYEDACTIONPRESENTATIONTIME calibration from none to miliseconds to reflect the units that was always defined for this calibration in the GIS-500. Also deleted the ENABLE_CLIMATECONTROL_QUICK_STATUS_PANE calibration from this caldef, as reference the calibration for the Quick Status Pane enable function is being added in the GIS550_ClimateTouchScreenUI_GlobalB.caldef file as a part of the calibration updates in this MY19 CAL Database Version 3.0.3 release. Also deleted the following eleven calibrations confirmed not to be needed: 1.) POPUP_DISMISS_KEY_DELAY, 2.) MINACTIVITYINDICATORENABLETIME, 3.) MEDIA_SOURCE_CHANGE_TO_NOW_PLAYING_TIMEOUT, 4.) ENABLE_POP_UPS_WIDGET_AUTOMATICDISMISSAL, 5.) D_SHORT_AUTO_ACK, 6.) D_MEDIUM_AUTO_ACK, 7.) D_LONG_AUTO_ACK, 8.) CANCEL_TIME, 9.) ALERT_AUTODISMISSFADEOUTTIME, 10.) POPUPWIDGET_AUTODISMISSFADEOUTTIME, and 11.) MINACTIVITYINDICATORACTIVETIME. Also, updated the description for the DEFAULT_AUDIO_TOUCH_FEEDBACK_SETTING calibration to match the description reflected in the latest version GIS-507. And, updated the default value of the DEFAULT_AUDIO_TOUCH_FEEDBACK_SETTING calibration to match the default value of On (True/enabled) referenced for this calibration in GIS-500 Section 5.3.2.1 Audible Touch Feedback Off/On.</Description>
    <Author>Ginnard Kimbrough</Author>
  </CalDefFileChangeRecord>
  <CalDefFileChangeRecord>
    <Version>12</Version>
    <Date>2/27/2017</Date>
    <Description>Within the DisplayGesturesAndTimeouts.caldef file, deleted the QUICKSTATUSPANEWIDGET_AUTOMATICDISMISSALTIME calibration since the GM User Interface Team (Mark Miller) confirmed this specific calibration was a  legacy calibration used for NGI that is not intended to be used for Info3.</Description>
    <Author>Ginnard Kimbrough</Author>
  </CalDefFileChangeRecord>
  <CalDefFileChangeRecord>
    <Version>13</Version>
    <Date>6/10/2017</Date>
    <Description>Within the DisplayGesturesAndTimeouts.caldef file added back in the following seven NGI legacy calibrations deleted in a prior release: 1.) MINACTIVITYINDICATORENABLETIME, 2.) MINACTIVITYINDICATORACTIVETIME, 3.) D_SHORT_AUTO_ACK, 4.) D_MEDIUM_AUTO_ACK, 5.) D_LONG_AUTO_ACK, 6.) POPUPWIDGET_AUTODISMISSFADEOUTTIME, and 7.) QUICKSTATUSPANEWIDGET_AUTOMATICDISMISSALTIME. Note, these seven calibrations are for F-Ten Info3 Low Radio use only since these legacy calibrations are still being used by F-Ten in software for the F-Ten Info3.0 Low Radio only. Also, updated the usage field for all of the calibrations in this caldef file to support the new &quot;Global A/B&quot; categorization in the CalDef tool.</Description>
    <Author>Ginnard Kimbrough</Author>
  </CalDefFileChangeRecord>
  <CalDefFileChangeRecord>
    <Version>14</Version>
    <Date>9/29/2017</Date>
    <Description>Within the DisplayGesturesAndTimeouts.caldef file, added GEM usage to the following calibrations within this caldef: (1.) ALERTWINDOWELEMENT_DELAYEDACTIONPRESENTATIONTIME , (2. ) CSHMI_TOUCH_EVENT_BUFFER_TIME,  (3.) DEFAULT_AUDIO_TOUCH_FEEDBACK_SETTING, (4.) ENABLE_FACEPLATE_VOLUME_PRESS_HOLD, (5.) ENABLE_FACEPLATE_VOLUME_TAP, (6.) ENABLE_MENU_AUDIO_TOUCH_FEEDBACK, (7.) FACEPLATE_FLING_MIN_VOLUME_POSITIONS, (8.) FACEPLATE_TAP_MAX_TIME, (9.) FACEPLATE_VOLUME_TAP_VOLUME_STEP_DELTA, (10.) FRONT_FAN_SPEED_ADJUSTMENT_SLEW_RATE, (11.) FRONT_TEMPERATURE_ADJUSTMENT_SLEW_RATE, (12.) POP_UPS_WIDGET_AUTOMATIC_DISMISSAL_TIME_1, (13.) POP_UPS_WIDGET_AUTOMATIC_DISMISSAL_TIME_2,  (14.) POP_UPS_WIDGET_AUTOMATIC_DISMISSAL_TIME_3, (15.) POP_UPS_WIDGET_AUTOMATIC_DISMISSAL_TIME_4, (16.) SCROLLBAR_PAGEUPDOWN_SLEWRATE, and  (17.) VOLUME_PRESS_HOLD_VOLUMESLEWRATE. Since these calibrations fell within the current criteria of requiring GEM usage, which are any calibrations that would be used for Low Radio Global B application. Note, excluded adding GEM usage to the F-Ten Low Radio only specific legacy calibrations within this caldef since these calibrations are only being used for the F-Ten Radio supplier, which does support the GEM.</Description>
    <Author>Ginnard Kimbrough</Author>
  </CalDefFileChangeRecord>
  <CalDefFileChangeRecord>
    <Version>15</Version>
    <Date>05/03/2018</Date>
    <Description>Within DisplayGesturesAndTimeouts.caldef, updated the default value of the ALERTWINDOWELEMENT_DELAYEDACTIONPRESENTATIONTIME calibration to match the default value reflected in the GIS-500 Version 5.4 of April 9, 2018</Description>
    <Author>Emmaanuel Oleka</Author>
  </CalDefFileChangeRecord>
  <CalDefFileChangeRecord>
    <Version>16</Version>
    <Date>27MAR2019</Date>
    <Description>Added 'ENTRY_VCU' and 'VCU' tags for initial creation of VCS compatible CalDefDatabase for version GIS-646 V6.0.0 release.</Description>
    <Author>Scott Rush</Author>
  </CalDefFileChangeRecord>
  <CalDefinition Description="Quick Status Panes auto-dismiss after 3 seconds (calibratable) of inactivity with the vehicle controls. The pane will immediately be removed from the display (no  gradual/slow fading).  (Note: This calibration is only be used by the F-Ten Info3.0 Low Radio supplier) " Name="QUICKSTATUSPANEWIDGET_AUTOMATICDISMISSALTIME" Usage="LOW,GLOBALA,GLOBALB,ENTRY_VCU">
    <CalID>_yr6UaE1AEeO3UM5MzM17kw</CalID>
    <Type>Integer</Type>
    <Version>3</Version>
    <CalDefChangeRecord>
      <Version>1</Version>
      <Date>26AUG2013</Date>
      <Description>Initial import on from GIS-344 derived CSV file.  Original CALDS block=hmi_display_interface_caln</Description>
      <Author>GIS-344 GIS-343</Author>
    </CalDefChangeRecord>
    <CalDefChangeRecord>
      <Version>2</Version>
      <Date>2/27/2017</Date>
      <Description>NGI Legacy calibration deleted from this caldef file because it had no intended use case for Info3.0 and beyond</Description>
      <Author>Ginnard Kimbrough</Author>
    </CalDefChangeRecord>
    <CalDefChangeRecord>
      <Version>3</Version>
      <Date>6/10/2017</Date>
      <Description>This legacy NGI calibration is being added back into this caldef for F-Ten Low Radio use only since this calibration is currently still being used by F-Ten for Info3.0 Low Radio only. Also, updated the usage field for this calibration to support the new &quot;Global A/B&quot; categorization in the CalDef tool.</Description>
      <Author>Ginnard Kimbrough</Author>
    </CalDefChangeRecord>
    <Integer>
      <Value>3</Value>
      <MinValue>0</MinValue>
      <MaxValue>255</MaxValue>
      <Resolution>1.0</Resolution>
    </Integer>
  </CalDefinition>
  <CalDefinition Description="To offer the user more time to make a final dismiss selection before the pop-up is unavailable the pop-up will fade into the background over a 3 second period (calibratable). UPDATE: ALERT_AUTODISMISSFADEOUTTIME must be in all CALDS bundles and common to all HMI software sets. * However the calibration only functions with 8 systems and shall have default of 3 seconds. * The calibration will perform no action in the 4.2 software sets and shall have default of 0 seconds. auto-dismiss fadeout is not described in GIS-402 and alerts will not FADE out. No transitional animation for 4.2 systems. (Note: This calibration is only be used by the F-Ten Info3.0 Low Radio supplier)  " Name="POPUPWIDGET_AUTODISMISSFADEOUTTIME" Usage="LOW,GLOBALA,GLOBALB,ENTRY_VCU">
    <CalID>_yr34N01AEeO3UM5MzM17kw</CalID>
    <Type>Integer</Type>
    <Version>3</Version>
    <CalDefChangeRecord>
      <Version>1</Version>
      <Date>26AUG2013</Date>
